            <p>Facts About Pollution</p>
            </style>
            <p>Did you know that...?
                <br>
                <br>1.)Pollution effects 100 million people!
                <br>2.)Over 1 million seabirds and 100,000 sea mammals are killed by pollution every year.
                <br>3.)People who live in places with high levels of air pollutants have a 20% higher risk of death from lung cancer than people who live in less-polluted areas.
                <br>4.)The Mississippi River carries an estimated 1.5 million metric tons of nitrogen pollution into the Gulf of Mexico each year, creating a "dead zone" in the Gulf each summer about the size of New Jersey.
                <br>5.)About 40% of the lakes in America are too polluted for fishing, aquatic life, or swimming.
                <br>6.)More than 3 million children under age five die annually from environmental factors.
                <br>"11 Facts About Pollution." 11 Facts About Pollution. Do Something, n.d. Web. 09 Jan. 2016. https://www.dosomething.org/us/facts/11-facts-about-pollution.
            </p>
        </div>
 
        <div id="tab2" class="tab">
            
            <p>The Solution to Pollution</p>
            <p>The excess of carbon dioxide in the air is an essential cause to pollution in the air.   </p>
